title: Chairs Johnson and Beyer Celebrate James Webb Space Telescope Reaching Orbit
summary: (Washington, DC) – Today, the James Webb Space Telescope (JWST) successfully reached its final destination at the second Lagrange point (L2). Over the next five months of commissioning, JWST will align its optics and calibrate its scientific instruments before the telescope begins collecting data.
